<subSubSection id="CE9353870F7485B93F0690A7149E236D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8C25156E298BB04A85D963D680E11980" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9541F200ADFAA7BDF8A6272474A8CDB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
European. A rare species described from Leningrad Region in northwest Russia (
<bibRefCitation id="11859D9CA49E187EA38F3BFAA3FCB99E" author="Ostroverkhova, G. P." editor="Bei-Bienko, G. Y." journalOrPublisher="Amerind Publishing co., New Delhi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR" year="1988">Ostroverkhova and Stackelberg 1988</bibRefCitation>
) and later found in a few places in Central Europe: Germany, Slovakia, Switzerland (
<bibRefCitation id="16E73C6073E3BB302ADB26A0C8FA70B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Chandler 2004</bibRefCitation>
), and from Vologda, Kostroma and Moscow Regions of northwest and central Russia (
<bibRefCitation id="09F016CE49431F9A5B0B674C1FCD2C33" author="Zaitzev, A. I." journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Fungus gnats of the fauna of Russia and adjacent regions. Part 1" year="1994">Zaitzev 1994</bibRefCitation>
). In Fennoscandia found from the Republic of Karelia (
<bibRefCitation id="BEE9FA82DDF450ED2461EDBF115D86ED" author="Polevoi, A. V." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Centre, Russian Academy of Sciences, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Fungus gnats (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae, Diadocidiidae, Mycetophilidae) in Karelia." year="2000">Polevoi 2000</bibRefCitation>
), Sweden (
<bibRefCitation id="80FA73FB0CD35056C6DDF47921AE05F0" author="Kjaerandsen, J." journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="1 - 165" title="Annotated checklist of fungus gnats from Sweden (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Diadocidiidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae)" volume="65" year="2007">Kjaerandsen et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and Norway (
<bibRefCitation id="643F4E78EE7BA2ED33AA508076F34AFA" author="Kjaerandsen, J." journalOrPublisher="Norwegian Journal of Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="147 - 171" title="Fungus gnats (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Diadocidiidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae) from More og Romsdal" volume="54" year="2007">Kjaerandsen and Jordal 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Included in the recent Finnish Red List, although here formally reported as a new species for the Finnish fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="87D806EB70946FF1E90382C08E560DBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="2CDD1EFF9D58EC5ECD8917F5F3793904" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7567D31084510D0D00E24340F9FC899" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
Finnish collecting localities are a herb-rich coniferous forest with a large proportion of birch and aspen in the southeastern Finland (Rantasalmi) and a sub-arctic mountain birch (
<taxonomicName id="6E1C46FD150BD6C150D8E6FF65964512" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="ssp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula pubescens" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subspecies" species="pubescens" subspecies="czerepanovii">Betula pubescens ssp. czerepanovii</taxonomicName>
) forest with herb-rich vegetation in the slopes of Saana Mountain in northwestern Lapland. Immature stages are unknown. Generally, 
<taxonomicName id="F72AA92356DB0AAFA958855E4C59C540" class="Insecta" family="Bolitophilidae" genus="Bolitophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bolitophila" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Bolitophila</taxonomicName>
larvae develop inside soft fungi (
<bibRefCitation id="D3684E81321712699DF22689E4000E62" author="Jakovlev, J." journalOrPublisher="Mycology: An International Journal on Fungal Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="11 - 23" title="Fungal hosts of mycetophilids (Diptera: Sciaroidea excluding Sciaridae): a review" volume="3" year="2012">Jakovlev 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6ABDD3B6A7F8DE8835FD1C71AAED5D2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="B6C090232BF5C589DFB3FB6F9F37E35E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Conservation</paragraph>
<paragraph id="657CD74F0BAA1C589D0DA4A472C5A1DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
